<h1>Unit 22 Section 6 : Volume of a Triangular Prism</h1>
<p>
This section looks at how to find the volume of a triangular prism.<br>
You will need to remember how to find the area of a triangle in order to do=
 this:<br>
</p><center><img src=3D"https://www.cimt.org.uk/projects/mepres/book7/bk7i2=
2/s6eg1.gif" width=3D"560" height=3D"184" alt=3D""></center>
<p>
A triangular prism has the same triangular cross-section throughout its len=
gth.<br>
</p><center><img src=3D"https://www.cimt.org.uk/projects/mepres/book7/bk7i2=
2/s6eg2.gif" width=3D"536" height=3D"255" alt=3D""></center>
<br>&nbsp;<br>

<h2>Example Question</h2>
The diagram below shows a triangular prism:<br>
<img src=3D"https://www.cimt.org.uk/projects/mepres/book7/bk7i22/s6eg3.gif"=
 width=3D"276" height=3D"153" alt=3D"">
<p>
<font color=3D"blue">(a) Calculate the volume of the prism if <i>l</i> =3D =
5 cm.</font>
</p><p>
<font color=3D"green">
Volume =3D area of cross-section =D7 length<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=
sp;=3D 10 cm=B2 =D7 5 cm<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=
sp;=3D 50 cm=B3
</font>
</p><p>
<font color=3D"red">The volume is 50 cm=B3</font>
</p><p>
<font color=3D"blue">(b) Calculate the volume of the prism if <i>l</i> =3D =
2 m.</font>
</p><p>
<font color=3D"green">
We need all the units to be cm or cm=B2, so we need to convert 2 metres int=
o 200 centimetres.
</font></p><p><font color=3D"green">
Volume =3D area of cross-section =D7 length<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=
sp;=3D 10 cm=B2 =D7 200 cm<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nb=
sp;=3D 2000 cm=B3
</font>
</p><p>
<font color=3D"red">The volume is 2000 cm=B3</font>
<br>&nbsp;<br>

